  </h3>
  
  <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
    <p>
      <span class="font-semibold text-green-600">Protected by HTTPS:</span> 
      Your messages are encrypted between your browser and this website using HTTPS, preventing network-level eavesdropping.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <span class="font-semibold text-amber-600">Vulnerable at Processing:</span>
      Once received by the website, messages are sent to n8n automation service over HTTPS (encrypted in transit) but are accessible in unencrypted form within the n8n service itself.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <span class="font-semibold text-amber-600">Third-Party Transmission:</span>
      After processing, messages are sent to Telegram through their API. Both n8n and Telegram servers can technically access the message content.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Data Storage:</span>
      Command history and message interactions are saved in your browser's local storage for convenience. 
      You can view this data with the <code>/age</code> command, disable storage with <code>/nosave</code>, or clear everything with <code>/clearstorage</code>.
      No message content is stored on the server.
    </p>
  </div>
  
